
Overview of verb coddle

The verb coddle has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (2) pamper, featherbed, cosset, cocker, baby, coddle, mollycoddle, spoil, indulge -- (treat with excessive indulgence; "grandparents often pamper the children"; "Let's not mollycoddle our students!")
2. coddle -- (cook in nearly boiling water; "coddle eggs")
